#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:1
msgid "Observability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:3
msgid "Production Metrics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:4
msgid ""
"SGLang exposes the following metrics via Prometheus. You can enable them by "
"adding `--enable-metrics` when launching the server. You can query them by:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:6
msgid "curl http://localhost:30000/metrics\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:10
msgid ""
"See [Production Metrics](../references/production_metrics.md) and "
"[Production Request Tracing](../references/production_request_trace.md) for "
"more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:12
msgid "Logging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:14
msgid ""
"By default, SGLang does not log any request contents. You can log them by "
"using `--log-requests`. You can control the verbosity by using `--log-"
"request-level`. See [Logging](server_arguments.md#logging) for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:18
msgid "Request Dump and Replay"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:20
msgid ""
"You can dump all requests and replay them later for benchmarking or other "
"purposes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:22
msgid ""
"To start dumping, use the following command to send a request to a server:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:23
msgid ""
"python3 -m sglang.srt.managers.configure_logging --url http://"
"localhost:30000 --dump-requests-folder /tmp/sglang_request_dump --dump-"
"requests-threshold 100\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:26
msgid ""
"The server will dump the requests into a pickle file for every 100 requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:28
msgid ""
"To replay the request dump, use `scripts/playground/replay_request_dump.py`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:30
msgid "Crash Dump and Replay"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:31
msgid ""
"Sometimes the server might crash, and you may want to debug the cause of the "
"crash. SGLang supports crash dumping, which will dump all requests from the "
"5 minutes before the crash, allowing you to replay the requests and debug "
"the reason later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced_features/observability.md:34
msgid ""
"To enable crash dumping, use `--crash-dump-folder /tmp/crash_dump`. To "
"replay the crash dump, use `scripts/playground/replay_request_dump.py`."
msgstr ""
